New Records: Harry Kane celebrated his 100th England cap with a double against Finland.
Key Match Events: Harry Kane scored twice, once in the 57th minute and again in the 76th minute.
Trent Alexander-Arnold provided key assists for both of Kane's goals.
Noni Madueke made a notable debut by assisting Kane's second goal.
Ezri Konsa was forced to withdraw after rolling his ankle.
Pre-Game Insights: Harry Kane expressed his ambition to score 100 goals for England.
Post-Match Reflections: Lee Carsley enjoyed his second win as England's interim manager.
Harry Kane's family was present and shown on camera during the match.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Harry Kane wore sparkly gold boots to mark the occasion of his 100th cap.
Frank Lampard and Ashley Cole presented Kane with a special cap before the match.
There were empty seats at Wembley despite a large crowd.
